text: Evie Millynn (born 23 November 1994) is a New Zealand footballer who plays for Western Springs AFC and for New Zealand. ==International career== Millynn was part of New Zealand U17 roster who played in the 2010 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup. She appeared in two matches. She was also a constant presence in the New Zealand U20 team. She was part of the roster in the 2012 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup, where she played three matches and scored one goal. Millyn was also in the roster that represented New Zealand in the 2014 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup, she played matches for her country.https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=323191/ In 2015, she was called to the New Zealand 23-roster that will play in the 2015 FIFA Women's World Cup but was an unused substitute. ==References== ==External links== * * Profile at NZF * * Eurosport Player profile Category:Living people Category:1994 births Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:2015 FIFA Women's World Cup players Category:Association footballers from Auckland Category:New Zealand women's association footballers Category:New Zealand women's international footballers
